      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "20478fcb_f0c10f16",
      "file_path": "catalog-be/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/be/servlets/TypesFetchServlet.java",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 200,
      "message": "I think this endpoint would fit better in DataTypeServlet and the dataTypeId as a path param rather than query param.\nAlso it would be more accurate to call it the name rather than id (to distinguish from the id which is in form <model>.<type>.datatype\nId suggest path: \"{dataTypeName}/models\"\n\nwhen moved to DataTypeServlet you can also probably easily use dataTypeOperation.getAllUniqueDataTypeUidsToModels() instead of the methods on ResourceBusinessLogic",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5269,
        "name": "Michael Morris",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
        "username": "MichaelMorris"
      },
      "updated": "2023-01-26 00:03:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "8c343093_2af298c3",
      "file_path": "catalog-ui/src/app/utils/service-data-type-reader.ts",
      "patchset_number": 15,
      "line": 49,
      "message": "We can support both files containing the tosca definitions header and \"data_types\" element and file without these using the following to remove when present:\n\n    private getDataType(fileContent:any) {\n        const index = Object.keys(fileContent).indexOf(\"data_types\",0)\n        if (index == -1){\n            return fileContent;\n        } \n        return fileContent[\"data_types\"];\n    }\n\nand passing the return from this method to readName etc\nWe also need a small change in the backend to support, see comment in CommonImportManager",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5269,
        "name": "Michael Morris",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michael.morris@est.tech",
        "username": "MichaelMorris"
      },
      "updated": "2023-01-26 00:03:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
